```javascript
export const findAnagrams = (subject, candidates) => {
  const normalize = (str) =>
    str.toLowerCase().split('').sort().join('');

  const subjectLower = subject.toLowerCase();
  const subjectNormalized = normalize(subject);

  return candidates.filter((candidate) => {
    const candidateLower = candidate.toLowerCase();
    // A word is not an anagram of itself (case-insensitive)
    if (candidateLower === subjectLower) {
      return false;
    }
    // Check if normalized forms match (same letters)
    return normalize(candidate) === subjectNormalized;
  });
};
```

**Key features:**
- Case-insensitive comparison for detecting anagrams
- Words are not considered anagrams of themselves (even with different casing)
- Uses character sorting to compare letter composition
- Handles Unicode/Greek letters correctly
- Filters out non-anagrams and words with identical checksums but different letters

